using SpecialFunctions
J₃(x) = besselj(3, x)
plot(J₃, 0, 20;
    title="Bessel function",
    xaxis=(L"x"),  yaxis=(L"J_3(x)"),  grid=:xy)
From the graph we see roots near 6, 10, 13, 16, and 19. We use
package to find these roots accurately. It uses vector variables, so we have to code accordingly.
. Here it sets a goal for the maximum value of

children.html: ∣f(x)∣|f(x)|∣f(x)∣

children.value:
using NLsolve
ω = []
for guess = [6., 10. ,13., 16., 19.]
    s = nlsolve(x -> J₃(x[1]), [guess], ftol=1e-14)
    append!(ω, s.zero)
end

r = []
for guess = [3., 6., 10., 13.]
    f(x) = J₃(x[1]) - 0.2
    s = nlsolve(f, [guess], ftol=1e-14)
    append!(r, s.zero)
end
